# Never copy host-built artifacts into the image. In particular, node_modules
# contains native binaries (better-sqlite3) compiled for the HOST OS (Windows);
# copying them into the Linux image causes "invalid ELF header". `npm ci` inside
# the Dockerfile rebuilds them correctly for Linux.
**/node_modules

# local SQLite data + datasets (the container uses its own volume + self-seeds)
backend/data

# vcs / logs / env
.git
*.log
.env
